#: ../../../user/misc.rst:10
msgid "Special values defined in numpy: nan, inf,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:12
msgid ""
"NaNs can be used as a poor-man's mask (if you don't care what the original "
"value was)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:15
msgid "Note: cannot use equality to test NaNs. E.g.: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:17
msgid ""
">>> myarr = np.array([1., 0., np.nan, 3.])\n"
">>> np.nonzero(myarr == np.nan)\n"
"(array([], dtype=int64),)\n"
">>> np.nan == np.nan  # is always False! Use special numpy functions "
"instead.\n"
"False\n"
">>> myarr[myarr == np.nan] = 0. # doesn't work\n"
">>> myarr\n"
"array([  1.,   0.,  nan,   3.])\n"
">>> myarr[np.isnan(myarr)] = 0. # use this instead find\n"
">>> myarr\n"
"array([1.,  0.,  0.,  3.])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:29
msgid "Other related special value functions: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:31
msgid ""
"isinf():    True if value is inf\n"
"isfinite(): True if not nan or inf\n"
"nan_to_num(): Map nan to 0, inf to max float, -inf to min float"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:35
msgid ""
"The following corresponds to the usual functions except that nans are "
"excluded from the results: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:38
msgid ""
"nansum()\n"
"nanmax()\n"
"nanmin()\n"
"nanargmax()\n"
"nanargmin()\n"
"\n"
">>> x = np.arange(10.)\n"
">>> x[3] = np.nan\n"
">>> x.sum()\n"
"nan\n"
">>> np.nansum(x)\n"
"42.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:52
msgid "How numpy handles numerical exceptions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:54
msgid ""
"The default is to ``'warn'`` for ``invalid``, ``divide``, and ``overflow`` "
"and ``'ignore'`` for ``underflow``.  But this can be changed, and it can be "
"set individually for different kinds of exceptions. The different behaviors "
"are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:59
msgid "'ignore' : Take no action when the exception occurs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:60
msgid "'warn'   : Print a `RuntimeWarning` (via the Python `warnings` module)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:61
msgid "'raise'  : Raise a `FloatingPointError`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:62
msgid "'call'   : Call a function specified using the `seterrcall` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:63
msgid "'print'  : Print a warning directly to ``stdout``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:64
msgid "'log'    : Record error in a Log object specified by `seterrcall`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:66
msgid "These behaviors can be set for all kinds of errors or specific ones:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:68
msgid "all       : apply to all numeric exceptions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:69
msgid "invalid   : when NaNs are generated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:70
msgid "divide    : divide by zero (for integers as well!)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:71
msgid "overflow  : floating point overflows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:72
msgid "underflow : floating point underflows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:74
msgid ""
"Note that integer divide-by-zero is handled by the same machinery. These "
"behaviors are set on a per-thread basis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:78
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/misc.rst:82
msgid ""
">>> oldsettings = np.seterr(all='warn')\n"
">>> np.zeros(5,dtype=np.float32)/0.\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"...\n"
"RuntimeWarning: invalid value encountered in divide\n"
">>> j = np.seterr(under='ignore')\n"
">>> np.array([1.e-100])**10\n"
"array([0.])\n"
">>> j = np.seterr(invalid='raise')\n"
">>> np.sqrt(np.array([-1.]))\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"...\n"
"FloatingPointError: invalid value encountered in sqrt\n"
">>> def errorhandler(errstr, errflag):\n"
"...      print(\"saw stupid error!\")\n"
">>> np.seterrcall(errorhandler)\n"
">>> j = np.seterr(all='call')\n"
">>> np.zeros(5, dtype=np.int32)/0\n"
"saw stupid error!\n"
"array([nan, nan, nan, nan, nan])\n"
">>> j = np.seterr(**oldsettings) # restore previous\n"
"...                              # error-handling settings"
msgstr ""

